en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-tax-obligations-and-income-declaration-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-tax-obligations-and-income-declaration-in-turkey/","name":"A Guide to Tax Obligations and Income Declaration in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-06-05T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-06-05T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"A Guide to Tax Obligations and Income Declaration in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-06-05T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-06-05T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about your tax obligations as an international student in Turkey. Filing your income declaration correctly can offer benefits. Click here for all the details!","name":"A Guide to Tax Obligations and Income Declaration in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-tax-obligations-and-income-declaration-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-tax-obligations-and-income-declaration-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-tax-obligations-and-income-declaration-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 id="gelir-beyani-nedir" class="wp-block-heading">What is an Income Declaration?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">An income declaration is the process of reporting the income earned by an individual or entity over a specific period to the tax office. This declaration is essential for calculating your tax liability. In Turkey, taxpayers are required to declare their annual income. The income declaration form serves as the primary document for the annual income tax calculation.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-egitim-alan-ogrenciler-icin-kilavuz" class="wp-block-heading">A Guide for Students Studying in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students studying in Turkey may encounter certain tax obligations during their education. These obligations can vary based on a student&#8217;s employment status, the income they earn, and other factors. The requirement to file an income tax declaration depends on the type of income received.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Tax Obligations for International Students Working in Turkey</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can work while studying in Turkey. However, they are required to pay taxes on the income earned during their employment. Students working in Turkey must file an annual income tax declaration. It is crucial for students to declare their income to comply with their tax obligations.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to Get a Tax Refund: Tips for International Students</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students working in Turkey may be eligible to claim a tax refund under specific conditions. A tax refund means getting back a portion of the taxes you have paid. You can follow the steps below to apply for a tax refund:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>File an Income Declaration:</strong> Declare your annual income.</li>
<li><strong>Gather Necessary Documents:</strong> Collect the required documents for your tax refund claim (e.g., payslips, proof of tax payment).</li>
<li><strong>Submit Your Application:</strong> Apply to the tax office to request your refund.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the Wage Income Declaration Threshold for 2025?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The wage income <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/gelir-beyani-ogrenciler/">declaration threshold</a> for 2025 is an amount determined annually in Turkey. Individuals who earn an income below this limit are not required to file an income tax declaration. However, this threshold can change every year, so it is important to follow the most current information. Definitive information regarding the 2025 threshold can be found on the official website of the Ministry of Treasury and Finance or through local tax offices.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Who is Required to File an Income Tax Declaration?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, the following individuals are required to file an income tax declaration:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>It is a mandatory declaration for employees, self-employed professionals, retirees, business owners, property owners, and other individuals earning income in Turkey.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Individuals in these groups are obligated to declare their annual income.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What Types of Income are Taxed in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, the types of income subject to tax include the following:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Wage income (salaries of employees)</li>
<li>Self-employment earnings</li>
<li>Business profits</li>
<li>Real estate income</li>
<li>Other types of income (interest, dividends, etc.)</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These types of income are taxed at specific rates.</p>
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the wage income declaration threshold for 2025?</h3>
<p>Employees who earn wage income taxed via withholding from more than one employer, and whose total wages (including the income from their primary employer) exceed 3,000,000 TL (<strong>4,300,000 TL</strong> for the 2025 calendar year).</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Who is required to file an income tax declaration?</h3>
<p>Individuals earning commercial, agricultural, or self-employment income, as well as those receiving rental income or wages from more than one employer, are required to file a declaration.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the different types of income tax declarations?</h3>
<p>There are different types, including the Annual Income Tax Declaration, the Withholding Tax Declaration, and the Corporate Income Tax Declaration.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Is a declaration required for rental income under 7,000 TL?</h3>
<p>Individuals earning residential rental income below the annually determined exemption amount are <strong>not required to file a declaration</strong> for that income.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-06-05T07:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:52:55Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'a-guide-to-tax-obligations-and-income-declaration-in-turkey';
