<h2 id="geleneksel-ve-modern-tip-arasindaki-farklar-hangisi-tercih-edilmeli" class="wp-block-heading">Differences Between Traditional and Modern Medicine: Which One Should You Choose?</h2>
<h3 data-start="82" data-end="105">1. Modern Medicine</h3>
<ul data-start="106" data-end="396">
<li data-start="106" data-end="189">
<p data-start="108" data-end="189"><strong data-start="108" data-end="128">Science-based</strong>: Works with clinical research and evidence-based methods.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="190" data-end="290">
<p data-start="192" data-end="290"><strong data-start="192" data-end="215">Technology-assisted</strong>: Uses modern tools like imaging, artificial intelligence, and robotic surgery.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="291" data-end="396">
<p data-start="293" data-end="396"><strong data-start="293" data-end="322">Emergency and serious illnesses</strong>: It is the primary approach for cancer, heart disease, and surgical interventions.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="403" data-end="430">2. Traditional Medicine</h3>
<ul data-start="431" data-end="727">
<li data-start="431" data-end="519">
<p data-start="433" data-end="519"><strong data-start="433" data-end="453">Historically rooted</strong>: Based on methods like herbal remedies, acupuncture, and cupping therapy.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="520" data-end="619">
<p data-start="522" data-end="619"><strong data-start="522" data-end="542">Supportive role</strong>: It is complementary for chronic pain, stress, sleep problems, and improving quality of life.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="620" data-end="727">
<p data-start="622" data-end="727"><strong data-start="622" data-end="641">Natural methods</strong>: Offers drug-free treatment options but is not always supported by scientific evidence.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="734" data-end="771">3. Which Should Be Chosen?</h3>
<ul data-start="772" data-end="1096">
<li data-start="772" data-end="835">
<p data-start="774" data-end="835">Modern medicine should be preferred for <strong data-start="774" data-end="802">emergencies and serious conditions</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="836" data-end="972">
<p data-start="838" data-end="972">For <strong data-start="838" data-end="893">supportive care and quality of life improvement</strong> (e.g., stress, mild pain), traditional medicine can be used alongside modern medicine.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="973" data-end="1096">
<p data-start="975" data-end="1096">The <strong data-start="975" data-end="999">healthiest approach</strong> is the combined application of both methods under the supervision of specialist physicians, approved by the Ministry of Health.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3>What are traditional medicine methods?</h3>
<p>They are supportive methods such as herbal therapy, acupuncture, cupping therapy, leech therapy, aromatherapy, and massage.</p>
<h3>What are the differences between alternative medicine and modern medicine?</h3>
<p>Modern medicine is based on science and technology, while alternative medicine relies on supportive, traditional, and natural methods.</p>
<h3>Which hospitals offer traditional medicine?</h3>
<p>It is practiced in GETAT centers in university and private hospitals, as approved by the Ministry of Health.</p>
<h3>What is the traditional healthcare approach?</h3>
<p>It takes a holistic view of illness and aims to improve quality of life through natural and complementary methods.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-06-01T11:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:52:47Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/traditional-and-modern-medical-approaches-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Traditional and Modern Medicine Approaches in Turkey","title":"traditional-and-modern-medical-approaches-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'traditional-and-modern-medicine-approaches-in-turkey' );
