</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Objective</strong></td>
<td>To provide academic or professional qualifications and to formally assess them.</td>
<td>To provide practical skills, life experience, or personal development.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Location</strong></td>
<td>Institutions like schools, universities, and language courses.</td>
<td>Home, workplace, internet, social settings, or daily life.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Is non-formal education formal or informal?</h2>
<p>The concept of &#8220;non-formal education&#8221; generally refers to more flexible and open-to-all learning processes that exist outside of formal education. In other words, it falls somewhere between formal and informal. However, since it doesn&#8217;t result in an official diploma, it is mostly classified as informal or semi-formal education.</p>
<p>Examples: community education courses, vocational courses for adults, hobby and skill workshops.</p>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What is Formal Education? Examples</h2>
<p><strong>Formal education</strong> is education that is offered by official institutions within the framework of a specific curriculum and program, and which results in a <strong>diploma, certificate, or official document</strong>.</p>
<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Characteristics:</h4>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>It is planned and structured.</li>
<li>A teacher or expert provides guidance.</li>
<li>Progress is measured through exams and assessments.</li>
<li>It is certified (diploma, certificate).</li>
</ul>
<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Examples:</h4>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Primary school, middle school, high school, and university education</li>
<li>Language courses (programs that grant certificates)</li>
<li>Vocational training courses and certificate programs</li>
<li>Official training seminars and workshops</li>
</ul>
<p>In short, <strong>formal education is official, planned, and certified education</strong>.</p></p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-05-31T11:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-16T19:52:45Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'learning-turkish-self-study-vs-formal-education' );
