e","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-accessing-academic-articles-and-resources-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-accessing-academic-articles-and-resources-in-turkey/","name":"A Guide to Accessing Academic Articles and Resources in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-28T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-28T10:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"A Guide to Accessing Academic Articles and Resources in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-28T10:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-28T10:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Explore the best ways to access academic articles and resources for your studies in Turkey. Click now to get started!","name":"A Guide to Accessing Academic Articles and Resources in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-accessing-academic-articles-and-resources-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-accessing-academic-articles-and-resources-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/a-guide-to-accessing-academic-articles-and-resources-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This article will provide a detailed look at topics such as the libraries you can use for academic research in Turkey, recommended academic journals, the process of publishing articles, and who is eligible to publish.</p>
<h2 id="akademik-kaynaklara-nasil-erisebilirim" class="wp-block-heading">How can I access academic resources?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, access to academic resources is provided through university libraries, digital databases, and open-access platforms. Here are the ways to access these resources:</p>
<p>There are many methods you can use to access academic resources. Here are some of the most effective ones:</p>
<h4>1. University Libraries and Databases</h4>
<p>If you&#8217;re affiliated with a university, accessing the resources offered by your university library is the best way to go. Universities typically have subscriptions to various databases (e.g., <b>Web of Science, Scopus, JSTOR, PubMed</b>) that provide access to thousands of academic journals, e-books, and articles. You can access these databases from within the campus or via a VPN from off-campus.</p>
<h4>2. Search Engines</h4>
<ul>
<li><b>Google Akademik (Google Scholar):</b> One of the most popular and easiest-to-use tools. It searches for academic articles, theses, books, and conference papers. In the search results, you can find links to PDFs of relevant publications or to the journal page where the article is located.</li>
<li><b>CORE:</b> This platform aggregates open-access articles. It only searches for publications that are freely available, making it ideal for those who have difficulty accessing resources that require a paid subscription.</li>
</ul>
<h4>3. Open Access Resources</h4>
<p>Many academic journals make their articles available for free. Here are some platforms for accessing these resources:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>DOAJ (Directory of Open Access Journals):</b> Lists fully open-access journals. It provides access to high-quality, peer-reviewed journals.</li>
<li><b>ArXiv:</b> A platform that hosts pre-print articles (preprints) in fields like physics, mathematics, and computer science. Articles are shared here before they are published.</li>
<li><b>ResearchGate and Academia.edu:</b> These platforms are social networks where academics share their own articles and work. The full texts of articles are often accessible here.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-akademik-arastirma-yaparken-kullanabileceginiz-en-iyi-kutuphaneler" class="wp-block-heading">The Best Libraries in Turkey for Academic Research</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are some of the key libraries in Turkey that you can use for your academic research:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Boğaziçi University Library:</strong> Known for its extensive collection and electronic resources. It offers an ideal environment for students wishing to conduct research.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Middle East Technical University (ODTÜ) Library:</strong> One of the largest libraries in Turkey. It provides access to both printed and electronic resources.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Istanbul University Library:</strong> A historic library, the Istanbul University Library has a vast archive and offers access to a wide range of academic resources.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Sabancı University Library:</strong> A modern library, the Sabancı University Library assists students with its research support services.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-egitim-alacak-ogrenciler-icin-onerilen-akademik-dergiler" class="wp-block-heading">Recommended Academic Journals for Students in Turkey</h2>
<p>Recommended academic journals for students studying in Turkey vary greatly depending on their field of study. However, here are some important journals and resources that are generally useful for many students and where you can find articles from different disciplines:</p>
<h4>Interdisciplinary Journals and Databases</h4>
<ul>
<li><b>TÜBİTAK Journals:</b> <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-tubitak-burslari/">The Scientific and Technological Research Council of Turkey (TÜBİTAK)</a> publishes high-quality academic journals across a wide spectrum, from natural sciences to social sciences. You can access these journals and many other local ones for free via <b>TÜBİTAK DergiPark</b>. This platform is one of the most important resources for academic publishing in Turkey.</li>
<li><b>DergiPark:</b> A service of TÜBİTAK, DergiPark offers a digital archive of journals published by universities and other academic institutions in Turkey. It provides access to articles in both Turkish and English. If you&#8217;re looking for a journal specific to your field, you can search on this platform.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Journals in Social Sciences</h4>
<ul>
<li><b>Amme İdaresi Dergisi (AİD):</b> An important journal in the field of public administration and political science.</li>
<li><b>İletişim Kuram ve Araştırma Dergisi:</b> Publishes articles in the fields of communication, media, and cultural studies.</li>
<li><b>Toplum ve Bilim:</b> Here you can find articles on various social science topics such as sociology, history, and philosophy.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Journals in Natural Sciences and Engineering</h4>
<ul>
<li><b>Turkish Journal of Chemistry / Biology / Physics:</b> Published by TÜBİTAK, these journals contain current research in their respective fields.</li>
<li><b>Journal of the Faculty of Engineering and Architecture of Gazi University:</b> Presents articles from different disciplines within the field of engineering.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Journals in Literature and Arts</h4>
<ul>
<li><b>Türk Dili Dergisi:</b> A long-established and reputable journal in the field of Turkish language, literature, and linguistics.</li>
<li><b>Hacettepe Üniversitesi Edebiyat Fakültesi Dergisi:</b> Publishes articles on various topics in literature and linguistics.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><span style="color: revert; font-family: inherit; font-size: 35px; font-style: inherit;">Where are academic articles published?</span></p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Academic articles can be published in various journals and at conferences. To publish an academic article in Turkey, you can follow these steps:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Journal Selection:</strong> Choose a journal that is suitable for your research topic. Review the journal&#8217;s scope and publication policies.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Article Submission Guidelines:</strong> Adhere to the article writing and formatting rules of your chosen journal. Each journal may have different guidelines.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Peer Review:</strong> Your article will be subjected to peer review by the journal&#8217;s editors and referees. This process is important for improving the quality of your article.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Publication Process:</strong> Once your article is approved by the reviewers, it will be published in the journal. The publication timeline can vary depending on the journal.</p>
<h2 id="kimler-makale-yayinlayabilir" class="wp-block-heading">Who can publish an article?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, the following individuals can publish academic articles:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Researchers and Academics:</strong> Academics working at universities can publish their own research in journals.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Graduate Students:</strong> Master&#8217;s or doctoral students can publish articles based on their thesis work or other research.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Independent Researchers:</strong> Independent researchers conducting their own studies also have the right to publish articles.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<div id="model-response-message-contentr_dc69e53fff22cebc" class="markdown markdown-main-panel stronger enable-updated-hr-color" dir="ltr">
<h3>Where can I access academic articles?</h3>
<p>You can access academic articles through university libraries, Google Scholar, open-access platforms (DergiPark, DOAJ), and paid databases (JSTOR, Scopus).</p>
<h3>What are academic databases?</h3>
<p>Academic databases are digital archives that index scholarly publications such as journal articles, theses, and conference papers. Examples include Web of Science and PubMed.</p>
<h3>What are national databases?</h3>
<p>National databases collect the academic publications of a specific country. For Turkey, the most important national databases include TÜBİTAK&#8217;s DergiPark and the National Academic Network and Information Center (ULAKBİM).</p>
<h3>What is a database in the context of a research article?</h3>
<p>In the context of an article, a database is a structured source containing the collected and organized data that forms the basis of the research. Researchers analyze this data to write their articles.</p>
